@NODE HISTORY "MappED History"
  @{B}V1.0, May 1994@{UB}
      Written just for the creation of a platform game @{I}(ZX81)@{UI} that I never
    finished and never will. The editor was a Blitz mode affair with
    no grid and a very suspect erase function which required pixel
    perfect clicking. No undo was included making map-making a
    harrowing business. Still, with patience you could make single
    screens (320x256) from the one set of shapes it let you use.

  @{B}V2.0, September 1994@{UB}
      I updated my ZX81 editor for use with an overhead Zelda style
    game I had planned. It was still the attrocious Blitz mode
    monstrosity, but undo was now included and a 16x16 grid could
    be used. The source code had to be altered to use different shapes
    in your maps.

  @{B}V3.0, March 1995@{UB}
      Another update for another game. The big step this time was
    allowing to select which game you were editing maps for. Sadly
    though it was from a pre-programmed list that had to be updated
    whenever files were changed or shifted. The grid was now versatile
    and maps bigger than the screen could be created.

  @{B}V4.0, July 1996@{UB}
      At last I attempt the awkward shift into Amiga mode and the
    world of intuition. The result is a hideous lethargic beast,
    that although friendlier than it's predecessors was simply to slow
    to use.

  @{B}V5.0, September 1998@{UB}
      At long last, an editor that is both friendly and multi-tasking.
    more versitile and better presented and much faster.

  @{B}V5.1, November 1998@{UB}
    Cleaned up a major bug in the scrolling. Stopped duplicate shapes
  landing on the same co-ordinates. Added extra keyboard shortcuts.

  @{B}V5.2, December 1998@{UB}
    Killed a major bug in the erasing of map blocks.

  @{B}v5.3, February 1999@{UB}
    Added Iconify option. 
    Added a (very slow) 'View map' option
 
  @{B}v5.4, February 1999@{UB}
    Fixed bug in the select shape window.
    Shapes can now be selected by double click.

  @{B}v5.5, April 2000@{UB}
    Improved editing of multiple layered maps, you can now view and
  edit single layers instead of viewing all layers at once.
@ENDNODE

@NODE BUGS "bugs. Bugs. BUGS. BUUUUUGS!"
@{B}@{FG SHINE}@{U} Known Bugs @{UU}@{FG TEXT}@{UB} 

@{B}Crash@{UB}
  This is an odd one. If you've had a few programs in the memory before
running MappED it might freeze permanently when you highlight shapes.
On other amiga's it can sometimes freeze on boot-up.
  Oddly, once the program is up and running and you've already
highlighted some shapes it never crashes and works just fine.
  More oddly however, I have had reports that loading Dpaint and quitting
it before running MappED, ensures that it runs smoothly and never crashes.
@{I}How odd.@{UI}  

@{B}Undo@{UB}
  Switching between erase and draw and using undo a lot will sometimes
cause oddness in the undo function overall. Nothing serious just odd.

  If you experience any more bugs, or think you know what's causing these
please tell @{"me" LINK ME}.
@ENDNODE

